President Obama announced his intent to nominate Herbert M. Allison, Jr. as Assistant Secretary for Financial Stability at the Department of the Treasury. Allison was previously the President and CEO of Fannie Mae and has extensive experience in the financial industry. He is currently a director of Time Warner Inc. and a member of various advisory boards. President Obama also announced the nomination of William J. Wilkins as Chief Counsel for the Internal Revenue Service. Wilkins is a partner at Wilmer Cutler Pickering Hale and Dorr LLP and has a broad tax practice. He has previously served as Staff Director and Chief Counsel of the United States Senate Committee on Finance. Wilkins is currently the Chair of the Section of Taxation of the American Bar Association.